                <head>No. 127.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Washburne</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-01-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 15, 1871</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 375.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith a translation of a note<note
                        n="*" xml:id="d127fn1">For note see inclosure to dispatch from United States
                        minister to Mexico of December 18, 1871.</note> of the 15th ultimo,
                    addressed to the United States minister at Mexico by the minister for foreign
                    affairs, concerning the good offices extended by you to Mexican citizens in
                    France.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
